{
  "texts": [
    "Hybrid Mamba-Transformer BackboneThe primary contribution of this work is a novel hybrid backbone that strategically combines Mamba and Transformer blocks.",
    "Our design is motivated by the hypothesis that Mamba and Transformers have complementary strengths for road segmentation.",
    "This hypothesis is directly informed by prior work on long-range benchmarks.",
    "The task of road segmentation, especially with occlusions, is functionally analogous to the Path-X benchmark [34], where the challenge is to identify a logically continuous path composed of visually discontinuous dashes.",
    "These interruptions are a direct proxy for the challenge of tracing a road network that is intermittently hidden by occlusions like trees and shadows."
  ]
}